{
    "Body": " Bridge the Exodus client with our new server infrastructure Description: Are you a Node.js old-timer who fell in love with DevOps? If the answer is yes, then read on. Exodus is a desktop client built on Electron which leverages backend Node.js services to connect to the blockchain asset networks. As a Senior Node.js + Devops Engineer, you will deploy Node.js applications that depend upon individual cryptocurrency daemons using AWS servers. What You Will Do: - Deploy Node.js applications into the appropriate pipeline (development, staging, production). - Build zero-downtime deployment infrastructure. - Review Node.js server code and submit pull-requests to aid in the deployment. - Use configuration management tools like Ansible to consistently configure server infrastructure in the cloud. - Use Terraform to build infrastructure. - Leverage container technology like Docker, Kubernetes, or AWS offerings to increase the efficiency of building and deploying services. - Build a geo-distributed infrastructure. Who You Are: - You are based in the US (preferred). - You have excellent references and a history of trust and established relationships in former careers. - You have a long history and track record of Node.js development that can be demonstrated via Github. - You take initiative and don't wait for direction. - You have a passion for cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin and demonstrated passion for solving problems. - You don't care if the platform is Azure or AWS and are willing to work with either and have some experience with at least one. - Willing to be available regardless of when server issues occur. Salary is paid in Bitcoin (BTC) Skills Node.js, PostgreSQL, AWS, Dockers Compensation $100,000 - $200,000 USD yearly paid in BTC + Equity Applications for this job are currently closed. ", 
